Description





Scenario:

UA High School is implementing a centralized School Management System to manage operations efficiently. To ensure consistency and prevent duplication, the system must follow the Singleton Pattern, allowing only one instance of the system to exist throughout the application.

As a developer, your task is to build this system using the Singleton Pattern. Administrators should be able to set and retrieve the school name, ensuring a single, consistent instance is maintained.

Functionality:

In public class Highschool,

-       Implement the Singleton Pattern to ensure only one instance of the Highschool class is created.

-       Use a private constructor to prevent the creation of additional instances of the class.

-       Provide a static method to return the single instance of the system.

 

